Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Most parameters are within normal limits. Mildly elevated creatinine may indicate early renal impairment or dehydration; consider follow-up and assessment of renal function. Slightly low total CO₂ could suggest mild metabolic acidosis or compensation; clinical correlation is advised. Glucose control (HbA1c) is at the upper normal limit, so monitoring for diabetes risk is recommended. Lipid profile is satisfactory.
